<h3>Free Commercial Version by filling email</h3>

<p>2012-04-29 11:08 星期日</p>

<p>http://cdn.sencha.io/touch/sencha-touch-2.0.1-commercial.zip,&nbsp;53 MB</p>

<p>First, unzip the archive to your local web server and navigate to&nbsp;http://localhost/your-touch-install/&nbsp;to view the documentation and complete working examples. Any samples that use Ajax will need to be on an web server in order to work correctly.</p>

<ol>
	<li>
	<p>Get Started</p>

	<p>Check out the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.sencha.com/learn/getting-started-with-sencha-touch-2/">Getting Started with Sencha Touch 2</a>&nbsp;guide to learn the fundamentals and create a Sencha Touch 2 Hello World example. Next, go through the&nbsp;<a href="http://docs.sencha.com/touch/2-0/#!/guide/first_app">First Application</a>&nbsp;guide to create a Sencha Touch 2 application in around 15 min.</p>

	<p>Visit the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.sencha.com/learn">Sencha Learning Center</a>&nbsp;for more helpful guides and tutorials.</p>

	<ul>
		<li>
		<p>Find&nbsp;<a href="http://www.sencha.com/learn/getting-started-with-sencha-touch-2/">Getting Started with Sencha Touch 2</a>&nbsp;here:&nbsp;http://localhost/sencha-touch-2.0.1/docs/#!/guide/getting_started</p>

		<ul>
			<li>
			<p>First, you&#39;ll need to download the free Sencha Touch 2 SDK and SDK Tools from the Sencha website.</p>

			<p>OK, Sencha Touch 2 SDK is just&nbsp;sencha-touch-2.0.1-commercial.zip</p>

			<p>And, SDK Tools is <a href="http://cdn.sencha.io/sdk-tools/SenchaSDKTools-2.0.0-beta3-osx.app.zip">Version 2.0.0 Beta 3 for Mac</a></p>
			</li>
			<li>
			<p>You&#39;ll also need:</p>
			A web server running locally on your computer

			<p>A modern web browser; Chrome and Safari are recommended</p>
			</li>
			<li>
			<p>Unzip&nbsp;SenchaSDKTools-2.0.0-beta3-osx.app.zip and double click SenchaSDKTools-2.0.0-beta3-osx.app to install. Then open a new Terminal and&nbsp;cd to $webroot/sencha-touch-2.0.1/ and execute command &quot;$ sencha&quot; to see what is displayed.</p>
			</li>
			<li>
			<p>Generating your first app</p>

			<p>Now you have Sencha Touch and the SDK Tools installed, lets generate an application. Make sure you&#39;re still in the Sencha Touch SDK folder, and type the following:</p>

			<p>2012-06-18 23:45<br />
			(Sencha Touch SDK folder means something like .../manuals/sencha-touch-2.0.1)</p>

			<pre>
$ sencha generate app GS ../GS
[INFO] Created file /Users/nickpoulden/Projects/sencha/GS/.senchasdk
[INFO] Created file /Users/nickpoulden/Projects/sencha/GS/index.html
[INFO] Created file /Users/nickpoulden/Projects/sencha/GS/app.js
...

Below is my another example:
$ pwd
/Library/WebServer/Documents/manuals/sencha-touch-2.0.1
$ sencha generate app senchaExample ../../SenchaTouch2Example/</pre>

			<p>This will generate a skeleton Sencha Touch application namespaced to the&nbsp;GS&nbsp;variable (short for Getting Started) and located in the directory../GS&nbsp;(one level up from the Sencha Touch SDK directory). The skeleton app contains all the files you need to create a Touch application, including the default index.html, a copy of the Touch SDK, CSS, images and configuration files for packaging your app for native.</p>

			<p>Note: make sure the up level directory&nbsp;of GS is writable for current user, or you will have to add &quot;sudo&quot; and cause&nbsp;&quot;SENCHA_SDK_TOOLS_2_0_0_BETA3 environment variable is not set&quot;</p>
			</li>
		</ul>
		</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Take a Spin</p>

	<p>Wondered what&rsquo;s possible with Sencha Touch? This&nbsp;SDK&nbsp;includes a whole suite of&nbsp;<a href="http://www.sencha.com/products/touch/download/sencha-touch-2.0.1/demos/">examples</a>. View with a desktop WebKit browser such as&nbsp;<a href="http://www.google.com/chrome">Google Chrome</a>,&nbsp;<a href="http://www.apple.com/safari/">Apple Safari</a>, or with a mobile emulator such as those in the&nbsp;<a href="http://developer.android.com/sdk/index.html">Android</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href="http://developer.apple.com/xcode/">Xcode</a>&nbsp;SDKs.</p>

	<p>Even better, visit the&nbsp;<a href="http://dev.sencha.com/deploy/touch/examples/">Sencha Touch examples</a>&nbsp;online with your own mobile device.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Become a Guru (Or Find One!)</p>

	<p>It&rsquo;s worth knowing your way around the definitive&nbsp;<a href="http://docs.sencha.com/touch/">Sencha Touch&nbsp;API&nbsp;documentation</a>. Be sure to check out the documented source code for our examples and demos.</p>

	<p>Our&nbsp;<a href="http://www.sencha.com/forum/">forums</a>&nbsp;are filled with talented and friendly professionals, and&nbsp;<a href="http://www.sencha.com/meetups">lively meetups</a>&nbsp;are held around the world. Finally, make sure you check out&nbsp;<a href="http://www.senchadevs.com/">SenchaDevs</a>, the definitive list of Sencha developers, to promote your skills or find partners.</p>
	</li>
</ol>

